---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const lastUpdated = 'April 2026';
---
<Base title="Terms of use" description="UroRef terms of use — clinical disclaimer, acceptable use, and licence terms.">

  <section class="u-hero" style="padding: 5rem 1.5rem 4rem;">
    <div class="u-hero-bg" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="u-hero-grid" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div style="max-width: 750px; margin: 0 auto; position: relative;">
      <div class="u-eyebrow-pill" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Legal</div>
      <h1 class="u-gradient-text" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">Terms of use</h1>
      <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65); font-size: 1rem; margin: 0;">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem 5rem; max-width: 750px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <article class="legal">

      <p>
        By using the UroRef website (uroref.com) or the UroRef mobile app, you agree to these
        terms. If you do not agree, please do not use UroRef.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Clinical disclaimer (read this)</h2>
      <p>
        UroRef is a <strong>quick-reference tool for trained clinicians</strong>. It is not
        medical advice, and it is not a substitute for:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>your own clinical judgement;</li>
        <li>your trust or hospital's local guidelines and protocols;</li>
        <li>senior advice from a consultant or specialist;</li>
        <li>the BNF, EMC or your local formulary for drug doses.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Always verify drug doses, contraindications and clinical decisions against authoritative
        sources before acting on them. UroRef is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind.
        The author accepts no liability for clinical decisions made using this tool.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Who can use UroRef</h2>
      <p>
        UroRef is intended for healthcare professionals — primarily urology trainees, registrars,
        consultants, and allied healthcare staff. It is <strong>not</strong> intended as a
        patient information resource.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Acceptable use</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You may use UroRef for personal, non-commercial clinical reference.</li>
        <li>You may not republish, scrape, or redistribute substantial portions of the content without permission.</li>
        <li>You may not use the content to build a competing product.</li>
        <li>You may not represent UroRef content as your own clinical authorship.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        Content, design, and brand are © UroRef / Nity G. Open-source dependencies are used under
        their respective licences. The UroRef name and mark are reserved.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Contributions</h2>
      <p>
        If you submit feedback, suggestions, or content via the feedback form, you grant UroRef
        a non-exclusive, royalty-free, perpetual licence to use that submission to improve the
        product. You will be credited where appropriate (e.g. for consultant content review).
      </p>

      <h2>6. Availability</h2>
      <p>
        We aim for the site and app to be available 24/7 but offer no guarantee. UroRef may be
        modified, suspended, or discontinued at any time.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any dispute is subject to the
        exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? Use the
        <a href="https://forms.gle/4QTK3MSgMsedJQEw7" target="_blank" rel="noopener">feedback form</a>
        and we'll respond as soon as we can.
      </p>

      <p class="legal-foot">
        If you spot a clinical error in UroRef content, please flag it via the feedback form so
        it can be prioritised for review.
      </p>

    </article>
  </section>

  <style>
    .legal {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.75;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
    .legal h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 2.25rem 0 0.6rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }
    .legal p, .legal ul { margin: 0 0 1rem; }
    .legal ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; }
    .legal a {
      color: var(--teal-500);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }
    .legal a:hover { color: var(--teal-400); }
    .legal strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 600; }
    .legal-foot {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background: var(--navy-700);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--r-md);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
    }
  </style>

</Base>
